In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims April 28, 2014, as Workers Memorial Day. He discusses the importance of workplace safety and the need to honor those who have been injured or killed on the job. The article highlights the contributions of the American labor force throughout history and the progress made in ensuring worker safety. The President emphasizes the government's commitment to improving standards and holding employers accountable for worker safety. He calls upon all Americans to participate in ceremonies and activities to remember those affected by unsafe working conditions.